12  Appendix 4 
5.  In particular, the editor and desktop publishing specialist will 
(i)  edit ADO parts 1 and 3 including (a) rewriting, reorganizing, or shortening the text 
to  improve  its  logical  structure  and  sharpen  the  arguments;  (b)  simplifying 
technical language, eliminating jargon, and introducing definitions so that the 
chapters can be understood by an educated nonspecialist; (c) coordinating with 
the authors and economics editors to make connections among ideas explicit 
and to illustrate complex concepts; (d) cutting or editing redundant passages and 
simplifying long complicated sentences; (e) smoothening or writing transitions 
between paragraphs and sections; and (f) suggesting additional materials (e.g., 
boxes, tables, figures) that would make the publication more reader-friendly;  
(ii)  check parts 1 and 3 for consistency and accuracy including (a) checking for 
factual errors (e.g., whether correct names of institutions and other entities are 
used; checking major statements of fact on leading websites of record, where 
practical); and (b) highlighting data inconsistencies (e.g., alerting ERMF national 
officers to discrepancies in data among text, tables, and charts for their chapters 
and ensuring that queries are addressed; and ensuring that the benchmarks are 
referred to coherently in the publication); 
(iii)  copy edit all parts of the reports in conformity with ADB’s editorial style and 
usage; 
(iv)  smooth out the entire structure of the publications to make it readable with a 
consistent logical flow; 
(v)  ensure, to a degree possible, consistency of language style; 
(vi)  ensure data integrity and consistency through data linking; 
(vii)  edit tables and figures; 
(viii)  ensure that subheads are consistent and logical; 
(ix)  check references to tables, figures, appendixes, bibliographies, and parts of the 
text; 
(x)  edit notes to make sure that the text references are correct; 
(xi)  supervise the encoding of corrections as well as incorporation of tables, charts, 
and boxes; 
(xii)  ensure a balanced layout of the manuscripts; 
(xiii)  supervise  and  implement  post-launch  changes  and  corrections  to  the 
manuscripts;  
(xiv)  review the final manuscript for digital printing (via PDF file); 
(xv)  prepare the terms of reference, definition of terms, and list of acronyms; 
(xvi)  edit all dissemination materials including press releases, speeches, questions 
and answers, key messages, and presentation slides;  
(xvii)  convert desktop publishing files to PDF format consistent with the ADB website 
guidelines; 
(xviii)  ensure PDF files submitted for printing conform with printer’s requirements for 
quality printing; and 
(xix)  perform all other functions as may be assigned by the assistant chief economist 
of ERMF. 

D.  Resource Persons (international, 1 person-month) 

6.  Selected staff from resident missions will be invited as resource persons during the ADO 
writers’  workshop  to  present  and  discuss  current  country  conditions  in  preparation for the 
drafting of the ADO country chapters.
